OL,3,CAntisemitism an 'urgent issue' for all
OL,4,Cof British society, Penny Mordaunt
OL,5,Cwarns
OL,7,FWriting in the Telegraph newspaper,
OL,8,Fthe pair described themselves as "hard-
OL,9,Fnosed politicians" who are "used to
OL,10,Fdealing with the extremes of human
OL,11,Femotions and catastrophe".
OL,13,FBut they added: "Even with decades of
OL,14,Fthese experiences, we were still
OL,15,Fstunned into silence by the evidence
OL,16,Fthat we received as independent chairs
OL,17,Fof the Board of Deputies Commission on
OL,18,FAntisemitism, particularly from young
OL,19,Fpeople in the Jewish community."
